Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uocculisrift.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Occulis Rift</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 8:10:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do I play the taxi?</span><hr size=1> I don't mind getting asked for ports.  You die, you ask for a rez.  You are 2 or 3 hours of walking away from your destination, you ask for a port.  Either that or ask for a sow.<br>
<br>
I like the idea of telling people your porting rate ahead of time.  I just look at porting as a plat per hour issue.  Don't get upset.  Make a macro that reads:<br>
<br>
/reply Sure, I will be happy to port you.  My current fee is 50pp.<br>
<br>
Or whatever.  Shift-SomeNum then SomeNumber are 3 keys you have to press to inform the person you will port for profit.<br>
<br>
I don't understand the attitude of, &quot;I'm a wizard - I hate porting!&quot;  Everyone has bad experiences with beggars and prima donnas who expect everything handed to them.<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm simple-minded.  I look at everything as a way to profit.  Either my wallet or my reputation profit from almost everything I do.  Even refusing to port people.  If warrior01 knows I cost 10pp for a port when I'm medding at the spires versus 500pp when I'm grouped with friends hunting... oh, I dunno.<br>
<br>
This post started as a rant and just kinda turned into a brain fart.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Can't wait till I'm of high enough level to charge people 1k for a port to the planes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualyssandra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alyssandra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 9:00:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do I play the taxi?</span><hr size=1> Let me put this in perspective <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Yesterday evening I log in and was in FV.  My guild and my eq husbands guild hunt a lot together and it was epic night for us.  So while I waited on him to finish his transaction someone, in fact two people asked me for a ride.  When I have nothing to do and they offer me money I will do it.  One of the people found a ride which was cool.  Other one gave me 100pp to take him to N Karana.<br>
<br>
Now when I landed in NK was where trouble started.  My server has some uber guilds that apparently feel a wizard is to be at their beck and call.  When I got free time I don't mind doing it but about only time I do it for free is when someone really needs help like CR.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind I have a Paladin and I learned the zones and have run them when I was unable to buy a port.  I don't whine directly to a person.  What happened is this:<br>
<br>
I land and I get asked in say... can you translocate me?  How any tank be unaware how irritating this is to <br>
wizards is beyond me.  First off he should have said it in ooc and not asked me directly.  So I calmly sent him a tell and asked for a donation.  Now this guy is in an uber guild, and he tells me, I am a monk and I don't have any coin.  <br>
<br>
So I chose to gate as I was in a hurry.  Maybe I should have told him I was busy, but it was the way in which he approached me.  Like I was a wizard and therefore I should translocate him.  I was also on roleplay which didn't seem to stop this dude any.  So I land in DL and not only do I get a few tells from him but from one of his guildmates.  So I told my guild and next thing I hear is.  Well if you ever need your corpse pulled from a tough spot I won't do it for you.<br>
<br>
Now at this point my guild got into it with the person and our mediator in the guild later that night had a discussion with one of their members.  Those two probably going to hear from their guild leader about this.<br>
<br>
Here is the thing tho... I did a mana calculation and a translocate saps me of 10% of my mana.  Now if one person asks for a translocate that isn't a problem.  But what if 5 or 6 do?  Then you have a situation that they want it for free and there you have to sit and med when you are there to play a game.  I do not believe asking for a donation should have resulted in this sort of behavior.<br>
<br>
I got told not only was I selfish but I was discourteous not to give him the translocate.  Obviously they subscribe to the theory that wizards are in the game for THEIR benefit.  Exactly the sort of thing I have been fearing ever since these spells have come out.<br>
<br>
I personally will only translocate friends and guildmates and before and after raids.  My down time takes away from something I can be doing for ME.  My guild leaders response was... they want a porter they can run a wizard on another account <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway that is my 2 coppers about the port business.  Sorry for the rambling.<br>
<br>
Alyssandra, 54 Wizard<br>
