 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uikeya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ikeya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 4:25:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do I play the taxi?</span><hr size=1> I port people for free. Do I port everyone who asks me? Nope. Those who start off with &quot;Can I get a port to DL plz?&quot; or &quot;Culd u port me 2 DL plz?&quot; I just either ignore or tell them I'm busy. If they are an orge or troll and do the second to me I tell them to knock the roleplay stuff of and speak normal so I can understand them. If they are roleplay or not a troll or ogre I usually ignore them. Why? If you can't take the time to say &quot;Can I get a port to DL, please?&quot; so I can easily understand you, why should I port you? Not only are you gonna take up my time, but you are gonna annoy me with your inability to type completely. Sure, its shorter, and saves time. But how long? Half a second? If they come on demanding and see me as there for their own transportation use, I ignore them.<br>
