I've never /auc'd ports for cash, and I've never explicitly charged a fee for a port.  Sometimes when it's a total stranger, I tell them &quot;I'll port you for free, donations are accepted&quot;.  Usually a guildie, freind, or anyone in a guild I respect just gets &quot;I'll take you for free&quot;, and I won't accept the donations from guildies and freinds, although I don't turn down whatever anyone else wants to give me for my &quot;free&quot; service.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is it's good PR and a nice way to make freinds.  And I bet I still make more money from ports than most people.  Hell, the other day a random stranger was so surprised by me porting them to GD for free that they gave me a Crystal Webshield and wouldn't take it back - stuff like that happens on a regular basis.  I generally turn down ports when I'm busy (be it solo or group) unless it's a CR or something else important, unless someone actually offers enough money to make it worth my time - but I still never tell them I need money to change my mind or how much.<br>
<br>
That being said - I still have trouble with groups.  It sure doesn't help your grouping to charge for ports - but even given my porting practices, I haven't been in more than one non-guild group a week for some time.  But then again, I don't look very hard anymore, I kinda gave up on it.<br>
<br>
 <p><BR>Cabot Coriolis of Tholuxe Paells<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaitop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>daitop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 10:33:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Porting</span><hr size=1> I have often ported strangers.  In fact, I've probably promoted bad behaviour since chances are I would port you if you sent a direct tell but wouldn't if you simply &quot;/ooc looking for a port to GD&quot;.<br>
<br>
I also rarely charged money and in fact have cancelled most trade windows when money was offered.<br>
<br>
Having said that I have observed a few things:<br>
<br>
i) Being a generous porter has never gotten me a group.  IMO we're kidding ourselves if we think people haven't forgotten our names 10 seconds after they've reached their destination and are eagerly playing the game.<br>
ii) People react more negatively to a refused port than they react positively to a given port.  When I port someone the most I usually get is a &quot;thks&quot; or a &quot;/bow&quot;.  Once however, while fighting in the Burning Wood I received a tell from a 55ish player asking for a port out since they didn't have sow.  I was in a group at the time so I responded &quot;sorry man can't leave my group but if you come to us we can give you a sow&quot;.  He then began to give me crap and the usual &quot;see if you get any help from me in the future&quot; crap.  Ironically, he was a cleric and I wonder if he just dumps his group whenever he gets a tell for a rez.<br>
iii) People will expect you to leave your group to port.<br>
iv) If you are in a remote location and can't port since it would take you 30 minutes or more to return to the location people will expect you to bind where you are regardless of how inconvenient the spot is or how convenient your current bind point is.<br>
v) People think that Translocates are a right.<br>
<br>
All in all I have probably generated more ill will in the 20% of the ports I have refused than goodwill that I have generated from the 80% of the ports I have given.  That is sad to say the least.<br>
<br>
I now simply reply with &quot;sorry...busy&quot;.  While it may not make me any new aquaintances it certainly saves me the aggravation of the many jerks out there who will berate you for a refusal.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaxxin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axxin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 10:33:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do I play the taxi?</span><hr size=1> When it comes to porting, I try to play the hardass, but I'm really a softy.  I charge a set amount, but if someone can convince me to make an excpeption, I usually will.  Ports for CR, if asked for politely, are always free.<br>
<br>
The reason I do this is to reinforce the idea that our ports are a privilege, not an entitlement.  I am under no obligation to port anyone anywhere.  If you ask me nicely, I'll probably port you for a token price, and sometimes for free.<br>
<br>
Remember, teleporting is a service, just like resurrection and SoW.  It's not unreasonable to expect compensation for services rendered. <p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="center">

